Durban - Police have arrested an alleged drug dealer from Wentworth, south of Durban, during an operation in the fight against drugs. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, police spokesperson, said while members were busy with their operation, they received information about a man who was on his way to deliver drugs in a flat on Silvertree Road. “The team kept observation on the premises and after few minutes the members went inside the flat. A search was conducted and a 26-year-old suspect was found in possession of 1 549 capsules of heroin. The total value of the recovered drugs is R47 000 and cash of R5 960 suspected to be the proceeds of drugs was also confiscated from the suspect. During the raid it was established that the suspect was supplying drugs to other dealers in the Wentworth and Merebank areas,” Zwane explained. He said the man was charged for dealing and possession of drugs and will appear in the Wentworth Magistrate’s Court on Thursday. “The team has proved that we are committed in cleaning our streets off from the drug lords. We also appreciate the information we received from the community about people who are dealing in drugs,” said Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner. Daily News